text: Arbor is an unincorporated community in Cape Girardeau County, in the U.S. state of Missouri. ==History== A post office called Arbor was established in 1884, and remained in operation until 1928. The community most likely was named for a brush arbor near the original town site. ==References== Category:Unincorporated communities in Cape Girardeau County, Missouri Category:Unincorporated communities in Missouri
title: Arbor, Missouri
